.TH "setup_purgatory_ppc64" 9 "setup_purgatory_ppc64" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
setup_purgatory_ppc64 \- initialize PPC64 specific purgatory's global variables and call setup_purgatory() to initialize common global variable.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" setup_purgatory_ppc64
.BI "(struct kimage *image "  ","
.BI "const void *slave_code "  ","
.BI "const void *fdt "  ","
.BI "unsigned long kernel_load_addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long fdt_load_addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "image" 12
kexec image.
.IP "slave_code" 12
Slave code for the purgatory.
.IP "fdt" 12
Flattened device tree for the next kernel.
.IP "kernel_load_addr" 12
Address where the kernel is loaded.
.IP "fdt_load_addr" 12
Address where the flattened device tree is loaded.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 on success, negative errno on error.
